id: pm-2p38
title: "Modular declarative authoring: mergeExtensionBlueprints + composeExtensionPackage"
description: "Complete the declarative extension-authoring loop with two missing assembly verbs. Today an author can describe an extension as one ExtensionBlueprint and turn it into a module (composeExtension) and synthesize its manifest (synthesizeExtensionManifest) — but (1) there is no way to build a blueprint MODULARLY across files (a commands module + a search module + a hooks module) and combine them, and (2) there is no single call that returns the whole shippable package (runtime module + on-disk manifest) from one declarative spec. Add mergeExtensionBlueprints(...blueprints) (pure, deterministic modular composition) and composeExtensionPackage(blueprint, identity) (author-once capstone returning { module, manifest } with the synthesized manifest set as the module's authoritative mirror so the two halves never drift). Author once, modularly; ship both halves in one call."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",authoring,dx
created_at: "2026-06-23T19:52:13.077Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-23T21:49:34.016Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: All three assembly verbs shipped (merge + package capstone + defineExtensionBlueprint); declarative loop author->merge->ship->preflight is end-to-end.
